.7894809554125955e-06, \"text\": \"France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The 2024 Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1335, \"to\": 1359}, {\"ngram\": \"an international multi-sport event\", \"from\": 1363, \"to\": 1397}, {\"ngram\": \"place\", \"from\": 1405, \"to\": 1410}, {\"ngram\": \"July\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1420}, {\"ngram\": \"August\", \"from\": 1427, \"to\": 1433}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Paris is the main host city, with events also being held in 16 additional cities across Metropolitan France, and one venue in Tahiti, French Polynesia.\", \"from\": 1455, \"to\": 1606, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1455, \"end\": 1460, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1870434857108938e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1543, \"end\": 1562, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999989801400004, \"rank\": 1.0198610257703944e-06, \"text\": \"Metropolitan France\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\"}, {\"begin\": 1581, \"end\": 1587, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"score\": 0.9999994414753669, \"rank\": 5.585248182848517e-07, \"text\": \"Tahiti\", \"types\": [\"Q23442\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tahiti\"}, {\"begin\": 1596, \"end\": 1605, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"score\": 0.999994078730447, \"rank\": 5.92130243547382e-06, \"text\": \"Polynesia\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Polynesia\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the main host city\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1482}, {\"ngram\": \"events\", \"from\": 1489, \"to\": 1495}, {\"ngram\": \"16 additional cities\", \"from\": 1515, \"to\": 1535}, {\"ngram\": \"one venue\", \"from\": 1568, \"to\": 1577}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Having previously hosted the Games in 1900 and 1924, Paris becomes the second city ever to host the Summer Olympics three times \\u00e2\\u0080\\u0093 after London.\", \"from\": 1607, \"to\": 1752, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1660, \"end\": 1665, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 1.1870434857108938e-14, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}, {\"begin\": 1745, \"end\": 1751, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"score\": 0.9999999999336069, \"rank\": 6.622373920479398e-11, \"text\": \"London\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/London\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Games\", \"from\": 1632, \"to\": 1641}, {\"ngram\": \"the second city\", \"from\": 1674, \"to\": 1689}, {\"ngram\": \"the Summer Olympics\", \"from\": 1703, \"to\": 1722}]}, {\"sentence\": \"This year marks the 60th anniversary of the establishment of diplomatic relations between China and France, and the Olympic Games presents another opportunity for the two countries to strengthen their bond and, by doing so, foster a cooperative spirit driven by the imperative of global progress.\", \"from\": 1754, \"to\": 2050, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1844, \"end\": 1849, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"score\": 0.9999999289307223, \"rank\": 6.390492875013958e-08, \"text\": \"China\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/China\"}, {\"begin\": 1854, \"end\": 1860, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/France\", \"score\": 0.9999942076564